After riding all night, she stops and dismounts. Looking down over her village, she takes in a breath of cool air. She watches the horizon where the sky meets the endless caspian sea. As she stands there, she closes her eyes. A small breeze begins to blow..<br>
the breeze grows stronger, and Areto grabs hold of her mare's reins to keep herself steady. The wind  begins to calm.. untill the air is still.. but areto can still her it rushing past her, whistling by her ears. The sound of wind turns to whispers.. faint and unclear, she listens. Her eyes open and she can see the clouds.. as they are slowly descending. She is listening.. not thinking, not dreaming., she hears.<br>
She closes her eyes and lowers her head, but with a soft breeze through her long, crimson waves.. she lifts it back up. Her heart pounding, as if to explode through her chest and escape her body.<br>
She mounts her mare and takes another look at her village. her breath leaving white vapors in the cold morning air. She unsheathes her sword, and tugs on the reigns. Areto and her mare ride swiftly down the way they came.<br>
